# NOTE: public/downloads/ (the hosted APK) is intentionally NOT ignored anymore -- see the
# "Fix APK parse error" note in the project history. It used to be gitignored on the assumption
# that a manual `firebase deploy` would always run right after copying in a fresh build, but
# GitHub Actions now auto-deploys hosting on every push, and a CI checkout never has gitignored
# files -- so every auto-deploy was silently wiping the APK from the live site, and anyone
# hitting the download link got served the SPA's index.html instead (renamed to .apk by the
# download attribute), which Android correctly refuses to install ("problem parsing the
# package"). Committing the .bin file is what makes it survive every future deploy.
